* make local (dev) version
- ./configure --platform macos --no-doc
- make

* make MacOS version
- make macos-dist

* make Win64 version
- make win32-pre
- on the Win32 side (VBox)
  . make sure the opam `lascar` and `rfsm` package are installed and up to date 
    (from a *Cygwin* terminal: `opam info lascar; opam info `rfsm`)
    If not, see ~/Dev/ml/{lascar,rfsm/rfsmc}/HOWTO to install
  . launch a *MinGW* terminal
  . cd /f/Qt/rfsm-gui
  . make win32-build
  . make win32-install
  . make win32-installer

* Build under Linux (ex: LinuxMint)

- install ocaml and opam: apt install ocaml; opam update
- get packages lascar and rfsm: opam install rfsm
- install Qt if necessary (qt5-default is pre-installed in LinuxMint 19)
- clone the source dir: from MacOS: make linux-pre
- on the Linux side 
  . cd /media/sf_SF2/Qt/rfsm-gui
  . ./configure --platform unix --no-doc
  . make 
